*simgear-0.3.6 (21 Oct 2004)

  21 Oct 2004; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org> -simgear-0.3.4.ebuild,
  simgear-0.3.5.ebuild, +simgear-0.3.6.ebuild, +simgear-0.3.7.ebuild:
  Two version bumps. Version 0.3.6 from: Alonso Schaich <AlonsoSchaich@gmx.de>
  in bug #59001. This version is required for flightgear-0.9.5 which fixes
  gcc-3.4 compile issues. Now, Version 0.3.7 is the newest upstream version
  for flightgear-0.9.6. This version from: Adam Babcock
  <ababcock@sympatico.ca> in bug #67809. Note that simgear-0.3.4 is removed
  from portage now, and 0.3.5 moved to stable for x86.

  18 Oct 2004; Luca Barbato <lu_zero@gentoo.org> simgear-0.3.5.ebuild:
  Marked ppc, this version works with gcc-3.4.1

  11 Jun 2004; Michael Sterrett <mr_bones_@gentoo.org> simgear-0.3.5.ebuild:
  ~amd64 for bug #52454; tidy

  19 Apr 2004; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> simgear-0.3.4.ebuild,
  simgear-0.3.5.ebuild:
  Adding IUSE.

  12 Apr 2004; Jason Wever <weeve@gentoo.org> simgear-0.3.5.ebuild:
  Added ~sparc keyword.

